Targets: Overall biceps

ğŸ”µ 2. Alternating Dumbbell Curl

Curl one arm at a time.

Allows better focus and reduces cheating.
Targets: Overall biceps

ğŸ”µ 3. Hammer Curl

Palms facing each other (neutral grip).

Great for adding thickness.
Targets: Brachialis + forearms

ğŸ”µ 4. Incline Dumbbell Curl

Sit on an incline bench (30â€“45Â°).

Arms hang behind you for a big stretch.
Targets: Long head (gives peak)

ğŸ”µ 5. Concentration Curl

Sit and curl with elbow braced on inner thigh.

Very strict, isolates the bicep.
Targets: Short head (inner bicep)

ğŸ”µ 6. Supinating Dumbbell Curl

Start neutral â†’ rotate wrist outward as you curl.
Targets: Long head + supination strength
(This is how you maximize bicep activation.)

ğŸ”µ 7. Zottman Curl

Curl up normal â†’ rotate palms down on the way down.
Targets: Biceps + forearms
(Great for balanced arm development.)

ğŸ”µ 8. Cross-Body Hammer Curl

Curl across the torso toward the opposite shoulder.
Targets: Brachialis (excellent shape-builder)

ğŸ”µ 9. Drag Curl

Pull elbows back and drag the dumbbells up your torso.

Less shoulder involvement.
Targets: Short head, upper biceps thickness

ğŸ”µ 10. Spider Curl

Lie face down on an incline bench and curl straight down.
Targets: Peak contraction, long head

